DataElementConcept.preferredName: Disease or Disorder Primary Immunodeficiency Syndrome Or Primary Immune Regulatory Disorder Classification
DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: Any abnormal condition of the body or mind that causes discomfort, dysfunction, or distress to the person affected or those in contact with the person. Unlike classical primary immunodeficiencies, susceptibility to infections is typically less prominent in these disorders._A method of generalization, the systematic arrangement of entities into classes or groups based on mutual similarity and certain differing characteristics.

ObjectClass.preferredDefinition: A definite pathologic process with a characteristic set of signs and symptoms. It may affect the whole body or any of its parts, and its etiology, pathology, and prognosis may be known or unknown.

PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Congenital Defects of Phagocyte Number, Function, or Both

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Congenital Defects of Phagocyte Number, Function, or Both
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A group of diseases or disorders caused by genetic defects within the immune system and comprising: Congenital neutropenia; Defects of motility; Defects of respiratory burst; and other nonlymphoid defects.

Concepts.longName: Congenital Defects of Phagocyte Number, Function, or Both
Concepts.definition: A group of diseases or disorders caused by genetic defects within the immune system and comprising: Congenital neutropenia; Defects of motility; Defects of respiratory burst; and other nonlymphoid defects.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A group of autoimmune disorders characterized by defects in self-tolerance (central or peripheral) resulting in autoimmune disease with or without recurrent infections, comprised by: Familial hemophagocytic lymphohistiocytosis (FHL) syndromes; FHL syndromes with hypopigmentation; Regulatory T cell (Treg) defects (eg, IPEX); Autoimmunity with or without lymphoproliferation (eg, autoimmune polyendocrinopathy with candidiasis and ectodermal dystrophy [APECED]); Autoimmune lymphoproliferative syndrome (ALPS); Immune dysregulation with colitis; and Susceptibility to Epstein-Barr virus (EBV) and lymphoproliferative conditions.

Concepts.definition: A group of autoimmune disorders characterized by defects in self-tolerance (central or peripheral) resulting in autoimmune disease with or without recurrent infections, comprised by: Familial hemophagocytic lymphohistiocytosis (FHL) syndromes; FHL syndromes with hypopigmentation; Regulatory T cell (Treg) defects (eg, IPEX); Autoimmunity with or without lymphoproliferation (eg, autoimmune polyendocrinopathy with candidiasis and ectodermal dystrophy [APECED]); Autoimmune lymphoproliferative syndrome (ALPS); Immune dysregulation with colitis; and Susceptibility to Epstein-Barr virus (EBV) and lymphoproliferative conditions.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A group of primary immunodeficiency diseases caused predominantly by antibody deficiencies, comprised of: Agammaglobulinemia with absent B cells; Severe reduction in at least two serum immunoglobulins, common variable immunodeficiency (CVID) phenotype; Severe reduction in serum IgG and IgA with normal or elevated IgM, hyper-IgM; and Isotype, light chain, or functional deficiencies with generally normal numbers of B cells.

Concepts.definition: A group of primary immunodeficiency diseases caused predominantly by antibody deficiencies, comprised of: Agammaglobulinemia with absent B cells; Severe reduction in at least two serum immunoglobulins, common variable immunodeficiency (CVID) phenotype; Severe reduction in serum IgG and IgA with normal or elevated IgM, hyper-IgM; and Isotype, light chain, or functional deficiencies with generally normal numbers of B cells.

PermissibleValues.value: Immunodeficiencies Affecting Cellular and Humoral Immunity Associated with Syndromic Features
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Combined Immunodeficiencies Associated with Syndromic Features

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Combined Immunodeficiencies Associated with Syndromic Features
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A group of genetic immunodeficiency syndromes with unique clinical features and well-characterized underlying immune defects, comprised of: CID with congenital thrombocytopenia; CID due to DNA repair defects other than forms of SCID in category I; CID due to thymic defects with additional congenital anomalies; CID with immunoosseous dysplasias; Hyper-IgE syndromes (HIES); CID due to defects of vitamin B12 and folate metabolism; Anhidrotic ectodermal dysplasia with immunodeficiency; CID due to calcium channel defects; and various other CID with unique clinical phenotypes.

Concepts.longName: Combined Immunodeficiencies Associated with Syndromic Features
Concepts.definition: A group of genetic immunodeficiency syndromes with unique clinical features and well-characterized underlying immune defects, comprised of: CID with congenital thrombocytopenia; CID due to DNA repair defects other than forms of SCID in category I; CID due to thymic defects with additional congenital anomalies; CID with immunoosseous dysplasias; Hyper-IgE syndromes (HIES); CID due to defects of vitamin B12 and folate metabolism; Anhidrotic ectodermal dysplasia with immunodeficiency; CID due to calcium channel defects; and various other CID with unique clinical phenotypes.

PermissibleValues.value: Immunodeficiencies Affecting Cellular and Humoral Immunity/ Combined Immune Deficiency
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Immunodeficiencies Affecting Cellular and Humoral Immunity - Combined Immune Deficiency

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Immunodeficiencies Affecting Cellular and Humoral Immunity - Combined Immune Deficiency
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A group of immunodeficiency disorders that include combined immunodeficiencies (CIDs) generally less profound than SCID.

Concepts.longName: Immunodeficiencies Affecting Cellular and Humoral Immunity - Combined Immune Deficiency
Concepts.definition: A group of immunodeficiency disorders that include combined immunodeficiencies (CIDs) generally less profound than SCID.

PermissibleValues.value: Immunodeficiencies Affecting Cellular and Humoral Immunity/ Severe Combined Immune Deficiency
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Immunodeficiencies Affecting Cellular and Humoral Immunity - Severe Combined Immune Deficiency

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Immunodeficiencies Affecting Cellular and Humoral Immunity - Severe Combined Immune Deficiency
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A group of immunodeficiency disorders that include T cell-negative, B cell-positive severe combined immunodeficiencies; and T cell-negative, B cell-negative severe combined immunodeficiencies.

Concepts.longName: Immunodeficiencies Affecting Cellular and Humoral Immunity - Severe Combined Immune Deficiency
Concepts.definition: A group of immunodeficiency disorders that include T cell-negative, B cell-positive severe combined immunodeficiencies; and T cell-negative, B cell-negative severe combined immunodeficiencies.

PermissibleValues.value: Defects of Intrinsic and Innate Immunity
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Defects of Intrinsic and Innate Immunity

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Defects of Intrinsic and Innate Immunity
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A group of diseases or disorders caused by genetic defects within the immune system, comprised by: Mendelian susceptibility to mycobacterial disease (MSMD); Epidermodysplasia verruciformis (HPV); Predisposition to severe viral infection; Herpes simplex encephalitis (HSE); Predisposition to invasive fungal diseases; Predisposition to mucocutaneous candidiasis; TLR signaling pathway deficiencies with bacterial susceptibility; and other inborn errors of immunity related to nonhematopoietic tissues.

Concepts.longName: Defects in Intrinsic and Innate Immunity
Concepts.definition: A group of diseases or disorders caused by genetic defects within the immune system, comprised by: Mendelian susceptibility to mycobacterial disease (MSMD); Epidermodysplasia verruciformis (HPV); Predisposition to severe viral infection; Herpes simplex encephalitis (HSE); Predisposition to invasive fungal diseases; Predisposition to mucocutaneous candidiasis; TLR signaling pathway deficiencies with bacterial susceptibility; and other inborn errors of immunity related to nonhematopoietic tissues.
